					</ul>

				</aside>
				
				
				<aside class="contact">
				<h4>Connect</h4>
					<ul>
						<li><a href="mailto:annieszaf@proton.me">Email</a></li>
						<li><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/annieszafranski/" rel="me">LinkedIn</a></li>
						<li><a href="https://typo.social/@annie">Mastodon</a></li>
					</ul>
					</aside>
			

			</section>

		<!-------------- EXPERIENCE -------------->

			<section id="info-text">

				<h1 class="info">Hi, I’m Annie. I’m an independent graphic and type designer based in Southern California.</h1>
				<p>I’ve spent over 10 years designing in-house, working across brand, interactive, and product teams as an IC, building up brands and designing websites. I have worked on talented design teams at <a href="https://www.mixpanel.com/" target="_blank">Mixpanel</a>, <a href="https://www.compass.com/" target="_blank">Compass</a>, <a href="https://www.wearesaatchi.com/" target="_blank">Saatchi & Saatchi</a>, <a href="https://www.everlane.com/" target="_blank">Everlane</a>, and <a href="https://www.eventbrite.com/" target="_blank">Eventbrite</a>—all of which has inspired me to dive further into type in different ways.</p>
				<p>In 2024, I invested in myself by applying to <a href="https://letterformarchive.org/type-west-online/">Type West</a>, a year-long type design program through the <a href="https://letterformarchive.org/">Letterform Archive</a>. It has been a long-awaited dream, and am now part of the graduating <a href="https://typewest.letterformarchive.org/2024/" target="_blank">class of 2024</a>, and was a TA for the 2025 cohort. The program helped me see typography and my design practice in a fresh, detailed, and inspiring way—with more focus and clarity. 
				<p>I have since gone independent and started freelancing, working on a mix of logotypes, visual identities, and graphic design work, while working on my own type design projects. With that, I welcome new opportunities, big and small, for work, collaborations, and friendship!</p>
				<p>For inquiries, please get in touch over email: <a href="mailto:annieszaf@proton.me">annieszaf@proton.me.</a> To see more in-house brand work and experience over the years, please request a PDF.</p>
			</section>

		<section id="colophon">
			<h6>Colophon</h6>
			<p>This static website is designed and built by Annie Szafranski using <a href="https://astro.build/">Astro</a> and GitHub pages—it is a work in progress. The logotype is set in <a href="https://lineto.com/typefaces/pirelli-vip">Pirelli</a> designed by Masahiro Nakamura and <a href="https://lineto.com/information/designers/lineto-designers/weichi-he">Weichi He</a>. The Headline copy is set in <a href="https://www.typemates.com/fonts/resonay">Resonay</a> by <a href="https://www.typemates.com/about/andrej-dienes">Andrej Dieneš</a>. The primary body copy and smaller headlines are set in <a href="https://kontour.com/typefaces/utile">Utile Narrow</a>, designed by Sibylle Hagmann of <a href="https://kontour.com/">Kontour Type</a>.</p>		
		</section>
		<section id="colophon-grid-lines"><p></p></section>

	</main>


	<Footer />

	<script>        
		import "../scripts/menu.js";
	</script>
	</div>
  </body>
</html>
